FIRST_USER_MESSAGE='You are workstream B_android_ble_background.  Workspace root: D:\rehealthAI  Target repo: D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk  Approved task: B1 only.  Important: D1 has already connected Android feature evaluation to backend. B1 must not modify that network/feature evaluation flow except for safe dependency boundaries if absolutely required. B1 is only about making ring/BLE collection more resilient in foreground/background and ensuring collected data is saved locally first.  Before doing anything, read: - D:\rehealthAI\AGENTS.md - D:\rehealthAI\ENGINEERING.md - D:\rehealthAI\CODEX_ORCHESTRATION.md - D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk\README.md - D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk\BUILD_NOTES.md - D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk\docs\FEATURE_EXTRACTOR.md - D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk\docs\NETWORK_FEATURE_EVALUATE.md if it exists - D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk\codex-runs\2026-07-09\D_status.md if it exists - D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk\app\src\main\AndroidManifest.xml - D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk\app\src\main\java\com\rehealth\genie\ReHealthApplication.kt - D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk\app\src\main\java\com\rehealth\genie\ring\RingModels.kt - D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk\app\src\main\java\com\rehealth\genie\ring\RingRepository.kt - D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk\app\src\main\java\com\rehealth\genie\ring\RingViewModel.kt - D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk\app\src\main\java\com\rehealth\genie\ring\mrd\MrdBleRingRepository.kt - D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk\app\src\main\java\com\rehealth\genie\ring\data\RingDataDao.kt - D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk\app\src\main\java\com\rehealth\genie\ring\data\RingEntities.kt  Your role: You are the Android BLE/background collection owner. Your job is to turn the current foreground ViewModel-based collection into a more real-world collection flow that can continue low-frequency collection when the app is backgrounded, while respecting Android restrictions.  Core rule: BLE collection must be local-first. All collected data must be saved to Room before any later upload/evaluation. B1 must not call backend APIs directly. B1 must not upload telemetry. B1 must not call model-service. B1 must not implement /measurements/batch sync.  Allowed files/areas: - app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml - app/src/main/java/com/rehealth/genie/ring/** - app/src/main/java/com/rehealth/genie/service/** - app/src/main/java/com/rehealth/genie/work/** - app/src/main/java/com/rehealth/genie/notification/** - app/src/main/java/com/rehealth/genie/ReHealthApplication.kt only for dependency wiring - app/src/main/res/values/** - app/build.gradle.kts only if required for WorkManager/notification dependencies - app/src/test/** - docs/BLE_BACKGROUND_QA.md - codex-runs/2026-07-09/B_status.md  Forbidden files/areas: - backend - model-service - rehealth-android - Android network client - RemotePhmService / feature evaluation flow - production /measurements/batch telemetry sync - raw PPG/RRI upload - CVD feature extractor math - large UI redesign - model scoring  Implementation goals: 1. Inspect current BLE and collection flow. 2. Preserve existing foreground manual collection behavior. 3. Add RingForegroundService or equivalent. 4. Add notification channel for ongoing ring collection. 5. Add persistent foreground notification while collection is active. 6. Add start/stop APIs or intents for ring collection service. 7. Add WorkManager fallback or periodic worker if appropriate. 8. Respect Android 12+ Bluetooth permissions:    - BLUETOOTH_SCAN    - BLUETOOTH_CONNECT    - foreground service requirements 9. Preserve older Android compatibility where practical. 10. Add reconnection/retry guardrails:    - Bluetooth off    - permission missing    - known ring disconnected    - app backgrounded    - service stopped 11. Avoid aggressive battery use. 12. Collection interval should remain conservative, for example 15 minutes unless existing product logic says otherwise. 13. Save collected measurements/sleep/activity/signals to Room through existing repository/DAO path. 14. Do not put network calls in BLE service or repository. 15. Document manual QA steps.  Recommended architecture: - RingForegroundService owns background collection lifecycle. - RingViewModel may start/stop service but should not be the only long-running collector. - WorkManager can schedule conservative periodic collection or recovery. - MrdBleRingRepository remains the BLE/protocol adapter. - Room remains the local source of truth. - Network sync remains D/E2 scope.  Validation commands: From D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk: - .\gradlew.bat testDebugUnitTest - .\gradlew.bat assembleDebug - git diff --check - git status --short --branch  Use JAVA_HOME if needed: D:\Android_Studio\jbr  Manual QA checklist to document: 1. Fresh install. 2. Bluetooth off. 3. BLE permission denied. 4. BLE permission granted. 5. Scan ring. 6. Connect ring. 7. Manual heart rate measurement still works. 8. Manual SpO2 measurement still works. 9. Manual BP measurement still works if supported. 10. Start background collection. 11. Put app in background. 12. Lock screen. 13. Wait for one collection interval. 14. Confirm Room receives data. 15. Stop service. 16. Confirm notification disappears. 17. Disconnect ring. 18. Reconnect ring. 19. Kill app process. 20. Reopen app. 21. Verify no duplicate aggressive loops. 22. Verify no network upload from B1.  Autonomous Iteration Protocol: Do not stop after a shallow first pass. 1. Inspect current code and write a concise plan. 2. Implement smallest useful vertical slice. 3. Run validation. 4. If validation fails, diagnose and fix within allowed files, then rerun validation. 5. Repeat fix/rerun up to 3 cycles before declaring a hard blocker. 6. If validation passes, self-review against Definition of Done. 7. Search for:    - network calls inside BLE/background collection    - /measurements/batch usage    - raw PPG/RRI upload    - hardcoded unsafe intervals    - missing permission handling    - missing notification channel    - missing service declaration    - accidental backend/model-service changes    - broken D1 feature evaluation files 8. Fix issues found within allowed scope. 9. Rerun validation. 10. Only stop when Definition of Done is satisfied or hard blocker requires user approval.  Docs to create/update: - D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk\docs\BLE_BACKGROUND_QA.md - D:\rehealthAI\Android-apk\codex-runs\2026-07-09\B_status.md  Definition of done: - Existing BLE collection flow inspected. - RingForegroundService or equivalent exists. - Foreground service is declared in AndroidManifest. - Notification channel exists. - Start/stop service path exists. - Existing foreground/manual measurement flow remains intact. - WorkManager fallback exists or clear reason documented. - No backend/model-service calls from BLE service/repository. - Local Room remains first persistence layer. - Android permissions handled/documented. - BLE_BACKGROUND_QA.md written. - B_status.md written. - testDebugUnitTest passes. - assembleDebug passes. - git diff --check passes. - changed files listed. - known risks listed. - final git status shown. - no backend files modified. - no model-service files modified. - no rehealth-android files modified. - commit if possible:   feat(android): add resilient ring background collection  Start now. Continue autonomously until the Definition of Done is satisfied or a hard blocker remains.'
